                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Bosch Cornering ABS EVO:</span> Allows for hard braking even when leaned over, with a 'slide-by-brake' function for track use.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Ducati Traction Control (DTC) EVO 3:</span> Sophisticated traction control with a predictive strategy for maximum grip and safety.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Ducati Wheelie Control (DWC) EVO:</span> Managed by the IMU to ensure maximum acceleration without unwanted front-wheel lift.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine Brake Control (EBC) EVO:</span> Helps maintain stability during aggressive downshifts and corner entry.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Riding Modes:</span> Multiple selectable Riding Modes (Race, Sport, Road, Wet) with customizable power delivery and rider aid parameters.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>These electronic aids are not just safety nets; they are performance enhancers, allowing riders of all skill levels to push the boundaries of the motorcycle with confidence and precision.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Price and Launch Timeline in India</h3>
                <p>The Ducati Panigale V2 is a premium product, and its pricing reflects the Italian craftsmanship, performance, and advanced technology it embodies. The new engine and significant weight reduction, along with the updated electronics, suggest a moderate price increase over the current model.</p>
